# Documentation Organization Rules for Cursor AI

## 🎯 PRIMARY RULE: Documentation Location

**ALL implementation documentation MUST be created in `/docs/` directory, NEVER in project root.**

## 📁 Documentation Directory Structure

```
/docs/
├── implementation/           # Implementation-related documentation
│   ├── architecture/        # System architecture & design docs
│   ├── best-practices/      # Best practices & patterns
│   ├── development/         # Development workflows & guides
│   ├── features/           # Feature-specific implementation docs
│   ├── quick-start/        # Quick start implementation guides
│   ├── setup/              # Setup & configuration guides
│   └── user-docs/          # User-facing documentation
├── guides/                  # General guides
├── reference/               # Reference documentation & APIs
└── quick-start/            # Quick start tutorials

/stale-docs/                # Outdated/superseded documentation (gitignored)
```

## 📝 Documentation Placement Rules

### Before Creating New Documentation:

1. **CHECK EXISTING**: Search `/docs/` for related documentation
2. **MERGE IF EXISTS**: Update existing doc instead of creating new one
3. **CATEGORIZE**: Determine correct subdirectory based on content type
4. **USE DESCRIPTIVE NAMES**: Use kebab-case, descriptive filenames

### Documentation Categories:

| Content Type | Location | Example |
|-------------|----------|---------|
| System architecture | `/docs/implementation/architecture/` | `authentication-system.md` |
| Feature implementation | `/docs/implementation/features/` | `marketplace-grid.md` |
| Setup/configuration | `/docs/implementation/setup/` | `database-setup.md` |
| Development workflow | `/docs/implementation/development/` | `testing-workflow.md` |
| Best practices | `/docs/implementation/best-practices/` | `api-patterns.md` |
